  "texts": [
    "4) Cloud masking: Clouds can have similar spectral properties as snow, leading to misclassification.",
    "Cloud 6) Band ratioing and vegetation indices: Spectral band ratios like the Normalized Difference Snow Index (NDSI) and vegetation indices like the Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) are calculated to enhance the contrast between snow and non-snow surfaces.",
    "7) Image fusion: High spatial resolution imagery (e.g., Landsat, SPOT) is fused with high temporal resolution imagery (e.g., MODIS, VIIRS) to combine the advantages of both datasets, improving the accuracy of snow 305 cover mapping.",
    "Landsat sensor-captured images are susceptible to distortion due to various factors such as sensor, solar, atmospheric, and topographic effects.",
    "Preprocessing aims to reduce these effects to the degree necessary for a specific purpose."
  ]
}